laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix appears dilated up to 14 mm with wall thickening and mild surrounding inflammatory changes suggestive of acute uncomplicated appendicitis. There is no evidence of perforation. The liver, spleen, pancreas, bilateral adrenal glands, and bilateral kidneys are within normal limits. There are cholelithiasis without cholecystitis. There is no free fluid or free air in the abdomen. The sigmoid colon, rectum, bladder, and prostate are within normal limits. A few prominent inguinal nodes are noted but there is no pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy by CT size criteria.
